  "text": "Monthly seasonal streamflow series are non-stationary and present seasonal components that reflect the rainy and dry periods associated with the nearby rivers. Such components affect the performance of any predictor, linear or not [CITATION_1] . Thus, it is quite useful to employ some kind of deseasonalization technique to remove the seasonal components, reinserting them only at the end of the forecasting process. Equation (11) In summary, we applied the previously described ESN architectures to the forecasting of the series z(n) in training and test sets. At the end of the prediction process, the seasonal components are reinserted, allowing the performance assessment in the original domain of the streamflow series.",
